Present location: INSTITUT DE PAPYROLOGIE ET D'ÉGYPTOLOGIE, UNIVERSITÉ DE LILLE III [02/049] LILLE
Technique: WRITTEN WITH A REED PEN/REED WITH SPLIT NIB
Name: Documentary papyrus
Description: This papyrus bears but nine lines of an accountancy, the same one as on P. Lille 61 (a)-(c). A characteristic is that the three last lines have been are erased. Consequently, one is reminded of a draft, a preparatory text. Negligible traces of faded texts exist on the verso.
